0With%20big%20eyes%2C%20she%20pointed%20toward%20my%20stomach.%20%26quot%3BYeah%2C%20I'm%20pregnant%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BHow%20old%20are%20you%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20asked.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3B34.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BWow%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20guys%20start%20so%20old%20these%20days.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20laughed%2C%20then%20left.%20Later%2C%20I%20regretted%20not%20saying%20something%20%E2%80%94%20anything%20%E2%80%94%20to%20her.%20Because%20it%20was%20offensive%2C%20for%20so%20many%20reasons.%20I%20still%20wonder%20what%20her%20reaction%20would've%20been%20had%20I%20responded%20with%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20start%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3Eearlier%2C%20but%20I%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwomen-describe-having-miscarriages-in-public-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehad%20a%20miscarriage%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%26quot%3B%20Or%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20no%20idea%20when%20I%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3Estarted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20first%20time%20I%20was%20pregnant%2C%20I%20had%20a%20miscarriage%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20first%20time%20I%20was%20pregnant%2C%20my%2012-week%20ultrasound%20revealed%20a%20reality%20I%20hadn't%20prepared%20for.%20When%20the%20doctor%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Freproductive-health%2Fsigns-of-an-early-miscarriage%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etold%20me%20I%20miscarried%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20I%20was%20left%20with%20a%20grief%20I%20never%20imagined%20and%20one%20I%20didn't%20quite%20understand.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20I%20got%20pregnant%20the%20next%20year%2C%20I%20was%20overcome%20with%20fear%20that%20I'd%20have%20another%20miscarriage.%20At%20every%20appointment%2C%20I%20expected%20the%20doctor%20to%20tell%20me%20it%20was%20gone.%20But%20it%20kept%20growing%20%E2%80%94%20my%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3Eson%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20kept%20growing.%20And%20when%20he%20came%2C%20I%20knew%20how%20lucky%20I%20was%20%E2%80%94%20that%20he%20made%20it%2C%20that%20he%20was%20here.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20last%20time%20I%20was%20pregnant%2C%20just%20recently%2C%20I%20was%20consumed%20by%20fear%20from%20the%20moment%20I%20saw%20the%20positive%20test%20result.%20I%20just%20had%20a%20bad%20feeling%2C%20so%20I%20prepared%20for%20the%20worst.%20Because%20I'm%2037%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20considered%20an%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-parent-lessons-self-care-age-insecurity-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eadvanced%20maternal%20age%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%94%20I%20had%20an%20ultrasound%20at%20eight%20weeks.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfterward%2C%20the%20doctor%20explained%20to%20me%20that%20the%20fetus%20was%20measuring%20small%20and%20the%20heartbeat%20was%20weak%2C%20but%20there%20was%20still%20a%20chance%2C%20still%20a%20reason%20to%20have%20hope.%20I%20had%20to%20wait%20a%20week%20to%20repeat%20the%20ultrasound%20to%20see%20if%20things%20improved.%20They%20didn't.%20Seven%20days%20later%2C%20when%20I%20returned%20to%20the%20office%2C%20she%20told%20me%20the%20heartbeat%20was%20gone.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20wasn't%20prepared%20for%20the%20grief%20of%20my%20second%20miscarriage%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20learned%20then%20that%20preparation%20does%20absolutely%20nothing%20to%20protect%20you%20from%20the%20devastation%20you%20feel%20in%20this%20situation.%20It%20didn't%20matter%20how%20many%20times%20I'd%20told%20myself%20it%20could%20happen.%20I%20was%20aware%20of%20the%20probability%2C%20knew%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmy.clevelandclinic.org%2Fhealth%2Fdiseases%2F22438-advanced-maternal-age%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estatistics%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2035%20and%2040%2C%20your%20chance%20for%20miscarriage%20is%20about%2020%25%20to%2030%25.%20But%20the%20ultrasound%20with%20no%20movement%2C%20the%20silence%20of%20the%20technician%2C%20and%20the%20words%20%26quot%3Bno%20fetal%20heartbeat%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20sonogram%20image%20placed%20next%20to%20my%20urine%20sample%20%E2%80%94%20it%20all%20hurt.%20It%20put%20an%20abrupt%20stop%20to%20my%20plans%2C%20the%20dreams%20I%20had%20for%20my%20family's%20future.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20was%20the%20weird%20thing.%20Despite%20my%20constant%20worrying%20and%20that%20bad%20feeling%20in%20my%20gut%2C%20I%20had%20still%20been%20planning%2C%20dreaming.%20But%20I%20had%20to%20stop%20doing%20that.%20I%20had%20to%20stop%20doing%20all%20of%20it.%20And%20I%20had%20to%20cancel%20the%20meeting%20with%20the%20home%20renovator%20%E2%80%94%20no%20point%20in%20getting%20that%20extra%20bedroom%20now.%20No%20reason%20to%20make%20lists%20of%20names%20we%20like.%20I%20could%20eat%20sushi%20again.%20I%20could%20have%20an%20old-fashioned.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESuddenly%20being%20able%20to%20do%20these%20things%20again%20made%20me%20feel%20like%20I%20was%20going%20backward%20%E2%80%94%20a%20direction%20I%20wasn't%20supposed%20to%20be%20going%20in.%20I%20didn't%20have%20time%20to%20go%20back.%20I%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20going%20forward%20to%20something%20new.%20%26quot%3BAdvanced%20maternal%20age%26quot%3B%20kept%20echoing%20in%20my%20mind%20%E2%80%94%20a%20term%20that%20feels%20like%20a%20verdict%2C%20a%20reminder%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsi