0because%20it%20feels%20good.%20In%20the%20summers%2C%20we%20buy%20inexpensive%20roller%20skates%20and%20skateboards%20at%20Decathlon%2C%20though%20the%20only%20one%20of%20us%20who%20is%20really%20any%20good%20at%20either%20is%20my%2040-year-old%20partner.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20we%20take%20long%20walks%20in%20the%20US%2C%20it%20feels%20less%20enjoyable%20where%20we%20live%20without%20the%20backdrop%20of%20Europe%20or%20the%20ability%20to%20jump%20into%20a%20shop%20or%20cafe%20when%20we%20need%20a%20break.%20And%2C%20like%20a%20lot%20of%20Americans%2C%20we%20don't%20live%20near%20reliable%20public%20transit%20and%20are%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcar-free-in-the-suburbs-happier-healthier-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erequired%20to%20drive%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20most%20places%20we%20need%20to%20be.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20France%2C%20we%20are%20also%20a%20lot%20more%20adventurous%20with%20our%20meals%2C%20whether%20we're%20cooking%20at%20home%20or%20eating%20at%20a%20restaurant%20or%20caf%C3%A9.%20Last%20summer%2C%20my%20son%20tried%20more%20types%20of%20pasta%20than%20I%20knew%20existed%2C%20a%20feat%20he%20was%20enormously%20proud%20of%2C%20especially%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvegetarian-foods-that-make-you-feel-more-full-2019-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%20vegetarian%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20We%20like%20being%20surprised%20by%20the%20flavors%20of%20new%20and%20different%20foods%2C%20and%20we%20also%20like%20our%20tried-and-true%20favorites%2C%20like%20cookies%20and%20beverages%20that%20we%20only%20buy%20from%20specific%20shops%20in%20specific%20cities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cspan%3EEach%20place%20has%20its%20own%20feeling%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere's%20what%20I%20can%20only%20describe%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bvibe%26quot%3B%20when%20we're%20in%20France%20%E2%80%94%20he%20might%20still%20spend%20too%20many%20hours%20on%20his%20phone%2C%20but%20when%20we're%20out%20and%20about%2C%20we're%20really%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3Eout%20and%20about%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20And%20it's%20not%20because%20we're%20in%20vacation%20mode%20%E2%80%94%20as%20a%20journalist%2C%20I%20take%20my%20work%20with%20me%2C%20and%20he%20always%20has%20some%20kind%20of%20project%20or%20book%20he's%20working%20on%2C%20which%20means%20we're%20both%20spending%20plenty%20of%20time%20in%20the%20real%20world%2C%20too.%20It%20just%20feels%20like%20we're%20more%20present%20and%20in%20the%20moment%20while%20we're%20there.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOur%20home%20in%20the%20US%20is%20removed%20from%20the%20city%20center%2C%20so%20our%20days%20are%20typically%20quieter%20and%20less%20energetic.%20We%20don't%20necessarily%20move%2C%20mentally%20or%20physically%2C%20with%20the%20same%20speed%20that%20we%20do%20in%20Europe.%20At%20first%2C%20this%20made%20it%20feel%20a%20little%20boring%20when%20we%20would%20come%20back%20to%20the%20US%2C%20but%20lately%20it's%20become%20something%20that%20we%20are%20both%20able%20to%20appreciate%20for%20what%20it%20is%3A%20a%20cocoon%20of%20sorts%2C%20if%20you%20will.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20my%20son%20has%20moved%20more%20deeply%20into%20adolescence%20he's%20enjoyed%20more%20freedom%20in%20both%20locations.%20I'm%20not%20quite%20ready%20to%20let%20him%20hop%20on%20the%209%20and%20traverse%20half%20of%20Paris%20by%20himself%20yet%2C%20but%20the%20fact%20that%20I'm%20even%20thinking%20about%20it%20makes%20it%20a%20lot%20easier%20for%20me%20to%20drop%20him%20off%20at%20the%20mall%20back%20in%20the%20States%20with%20his%20friends%20for%20hours%20and%20have%20no%20idea%20what%20they're%20getting%20up%20to.%20At%2015%2C%20he's%20more%20or%20less%20in%20charge%20of%20when%20he%20goes%20to%20sleep%20and%20knows%20when%20he%20needs%20to%20wake%20up%20on%20certain%20days%2C%20but%20during%20our%20first%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-mom-bittersweet-changing-dynamic-with-daughter-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esummer%20in%20France%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20his%20sleep%20schedule%20evolved%20to%20essentially%20a%20midnight%20to%20midday%2C%20solid%2012%20hours%20kind%20of%20experience.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELiving%20in%20two%20countries%20has%20relaxed%20my%20parenting%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20ways%2C%20the%20same%20way%20it's%20given%20him%20a%20window%20into%20how%20other%20people%20live%20only%20a%20(relatively)%20short%20flight%20away.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparenting-france-vs-us-differences-similarities-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714904882000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6633ce7e10dfcda4096613ce%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparenting-france-vs-us-differences-similarities-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22My%20son%20and%20I%20spend%20half%20the%20year%20in%20France%20and%20the%20other%20half%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20Here%20are%20the%20parenting%20similarities%20and%20differences.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Stephanie%20Kaloi)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparenting-france-vs-us-differences-similarities-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Wall%20Street%20big%20shots%20may%20be%20forced%20to%20cancel%20their%20summer%20vacations%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20illustration%20of%20the%20Wall%20Street%20Bull%20with%20a%20suitcase%2C%20plane%2C%20laptop%20and%20palm%20trees.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6633d4d710dfcda4096617ef%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWall%20Street's%20fantasies%20of%20decamping%20to%20the%20Hamptons%20for%20the%20summer%20have%20been%20shattered%20by%20higher%20inflation%20and%20stock%20market%20volatility.%3Cp%3EAdobe%20Firefly%3B%20Jenny%20Chang-Rodriguez%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E2024%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20easy%20for%20Wall%20Street's%20speculators.%20There%20was%20an%20improving%20economic%20picture%2C%20a%20clear%20way%20to%20trade%20it%2C%20and%20the%20chance%20to%20take%20it%20easy%20while%20still%20racking%20up%20profits.%20Inflation%20canceled%20that%2C%20and%20now%20it's%20almost%20certain%20that%20Wall%20Street's%20summer%20is%20canceled%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%202023's%20glorious%20stock-market%20rally%2C%20the%20Street%20went%20into%20this%20year%20expecting%20nirvana%20%E2%80%94%20a%20combination%20of%20healthy%20corporate%20earnings%2C%20strong%20household%20consumption%2C%20and%20a%20final%20defeat%20of%20high%20inflation.%20The%20combination%20would%20put%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20on%20a%20glide%20path%20to%20cut%20interest%20rates%20%E2%80%94%20a%20move%20that%20would%20reduce%20the%20cost%20of%20debt%2C%20push%20stocks%20higher%2C%20and%20make%20consumers%20feel%20richer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20inflation%20proved%20stickier%20than%20expected%2C%20and%20those%20interest-rate%20cuts%20started%20to%20fade%20from%20view.%20First%2C%20Wall%20Street%20pushed%20back%20its%20prediction%20for%20the%20first%20cut%20from%20March%20to%20June%2C%20then%20to%20September%20%E2%80%94%20now%20investors%20are%20starting%20to%20wonder%20whether%20a%20cut%20is%20coming%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20isn't%20what%20we%20were%20told%20we%20were%20signing%20up%20for%2C%20that's%20for%20damn%20sure%2C%26quot%3B%20Justin%20Simon%2C%20a%20portfolio%20manager%20at%20Jasper%20Capital%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20going%20to%20get%20rate%20cuts%2C%20and%20everything%20was%20going%20to%20the%20moon.%20That's%20why%20people%20bought%20stocks.%20Now%20that%20seems%20relatively%20unlikely.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20hope%20for%20cuts%20faded%2C%20the%20performance%20of%20major%20stock%20indexes%20has%20become%20decidedly%20%26quot%3Bmeh.%26quot%3B%20The%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20has%20slipped%200.2%25%20since%20the%20beginning%20of%20March%2C%20when%20this%20new%20reality%20started%20to%20down%20on%20Wall%20Street%2C%20while%20the%20tech-heavy%20Nasdaq%20is%20down%200.7%25.%20But%20worse%20than%20all%20that%20is%20the%20potential%20for%20higher%20rates%20to%20stick%20around%20long%20enough%20to%20change%20the%20shape%20of%20our%20economy%20and%2C%20as%20a%20result%2C%20what%20companies%20have%20been%20making%20money%20in%20the%20stock%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20Wall%20Street's%20fantasies%20of%20decamping%20to%20the%20Hamptons%20for%20the%20summer%20have%20shattered.%20No%20leaving%20the%20interns%20and%20junior%20analysts%20to%20just%20run%20the%20same%20trades%20that%20worked%20last%20year.%20No%20set-it-and-forget-it%20strategies%20pushing%20up%20portfolios.%20No%20unquestioningly%20buying%20the%20dip.%20Inflation's%20stubbornness%20has%20injected%20the%20market%20with%20uncertainty%2C%20which%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20drives%20volatility.%20Unfortunately%2C%20uncertainty%20and%20volatility%20do%20not%20come%20with%20a%20%24100%20lobster%20cobb%20salad%20from%20Duryea's.%20They%20generally%20come%20with%20pain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhen%20doves%20cry%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWall%20Street's%20expectations%20of%20sailing%20into%20a%20smooth%20summer%20weren't%20entirely%20its%20fault.%20While%20Federal%20Reserve%20Chair%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-news-today-dow-sp500-powell-fed-rate-cuts-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJerome%20Powell%20tried%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20strike%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rates-cut-wont-happen-anytime-soon-federal-reserve-inflation-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20cautious%20tone%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rates-fed-pauses-increases-december-rate-cuts-powell-inflation-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFed's%20public%20projections%20for%20interest%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20signaled%20that%20multiple%20rate%20cuts%20were%20coming%20in%202024.%20To%20the%20world%20of%20finance%2C%20that%20sounded%20like%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-outlook-disinflation-federal-reserve-rate-cuts-goldman-sachs-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elittle%20victory%20lap%20over%20inflation%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20meant%20the%20US%20would%20likely%20stick%20a%20soft%20landing%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Goldilocks%20scenario%20in%20which%20prices%20stabilize%20without%20slowing%20down%20the%20economy%20so%20much%20that%20it%20causes%20a%20recession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20the%20new%20year%20began%2C%20things%20started%20to%20go%20awry.%20Inflation%20data%20showed%20that%20prices%20were%20still%20rising%20at%20an%20uncomfortable%20pace%20%E2%80%94%20the%20core%20consumer%20price%20index%2C%20which%20strips%20out%20volatile%20categories%20such%20as%20food%20and%20energy%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-cpi-food-energy-gas-prices-consumer-price-index-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erose%203.8%25%20year%20over%20year%20in%20March%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Fed's%20preferred%20measure%20of%20inflation%2C%20the%20core%20personal%20consumption%20expenditures%20index%2C%20has%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-first-rate-cut-outlook-june-inflation-data-pce-index-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eremained%20stubbornly%20above%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20central%20bank's%202%25%20goal.%20Economists%20started%20to%20doubt%20that%20higher%20prices%20were%20being%20driven%20just%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-prices-inflation-soaring-corporate-greed-profits-margins-wages-jobs-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecorporations%20opportunistically%20jacking%20up%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20pad%20profit%20margins%20%E2%80%94%20but%20rather%20something%20more%20enduring.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rate-outlook-fed-hike-chances-cuts-jerome-powell-economy-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWall%20Street%20really%20started%20to%20worry%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20its%20precious%20cuts%20weren't%20coming.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjamie-dimon-soft-landing-outlook-recession-inflation-jpmorgan-geopolitics-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJPMorgan%20CEO%20Jamie%20Dimon%3C%2Fa%3E%20reminded%20everyone%20not%20to%20get%20%26quot%3Blulled%20into%20a%20false%20sense%20of%20security%26quot%3B%20that%20a%20soft%20landing%20was%20coming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20the%20Fed%20admitted%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20even%20though%20the%20economy%20was%20on%20solid%20footing%2C%20%26quot%3Bin%20recent%20months%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20lack%20of%20further%20progress%20toward%20the%20Committee's%202%25%20inflation%20objective.%26quot%3B%20It%20kept%20rates%20at%20current%20levels%2C%20reiterated%20its%20commitment%20to%20data%20dependence%2C%20and%20said%20it%20remained%20%26quot%3Bhighly%20attentive%20to%20inflation%20risks.%26quot%3B%20In%20other%20words%2C%20there's%20still%20a%20chance%20data%20is%20telling%20us%20inflation%20will%20get%20worse.%20Some%20analysts%2C%20including%20Torsten%20Slok%2C%20the%20chief%20economist%20over%20at%20Apollo%2C%20see%20signs%20that%20it%20could%20turn%20south.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRising%20energy%20prices%20combined%20with%20the%20ongoing%20rebound%20in%20the%20manufacturing%20sector%20increase%20the%20likelihood%20that%20we%20could%20see%20an%20increase%20in%20goods%20inflation%20over%20the%20coming%20months%2C%26quot%3B%20Slok%20wrote%20in%20a%20recent%20email%20to%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20scenario%20like%20that%20could%20put%20the%20Fed%20in%20a%20position%20where%20it%20might%20not%20just%20hold%20rates%20at%205%25%20but%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rate-outlook-fed-hike-chances-cuts-jerome-powell-economy-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econsider%20hiking%20them%3C%2Fa%3E.%20At%20his%20press%20conference%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20Powell%20said%20hiking%20was%20%26quot%3Bunlikely%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20he%20didn't%20say%20it%20was%20off%20the%20table.%20He%20also%20didn't%20offer%20a%20guess%20as%20to%20where%20this%20persistent%20inflation%20was%20coming%20from%20and%20said%20we'd%20find%20out%20%26quot%3Bover%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Wall%20Street's%20language%20of%20probabilities%2C%20that%20means%20nirvana%20has%20become%20considerably%20less%20likely.%20This%20isn't%20to%20say%20that%20the%20economy%20is%20all%20bad%20or%20that%20there's%20no%20hope.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgdp-gross-domestic-product-first-quarter-economy-growth-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGDP%20for%20the%20first%20quarter%20came%20in%20at%201.6%25%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20lower%20than%20economists%20expected%2C%20but%20the%20underlying%20details%20were%20more%20promising.%20Unemployment%20is%20still%20near%20historical%20lows%2C%20and%20wage%20growth%20continues.%20Consumers%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhate-spending-consumers-economic-sentiment-retail-sales-inflation-gdp-growth-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estill%20spending%20that%20mone%3C%2Fa%3Ey%2C%20too%20%E2%80%94%20driving%20strong%20retail%20sales.%20On%20the%20business%20side%2C%20UBS's%20head%20of%20equities%2C%20David%20Lefkowitz%2C%20said%20in%20a%20recent%20note%20to%20clients%20that%20%26quot%3Bcorporate%20fundamentals%20remain%20largely%20solid%20and%20intact%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20about%2075%25%20of%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20companies%20that%20reported%20first-quarter%20earnings%20had%20beaten%20estimates.%20This%20is%20good%20news%2C%20of%20course%20%E2%80%A6%20unless%20it%20turns%20out%20to%20be%20bad%20news.%20The%20economy%20has%20to%20actually%20come%20in%20for%20a%20landing%20for%20it%20to%20be%20a%20soft%20one.%20If%20the%20US%20takes%20back%20off%2C%20we%20run%20the%20risk%20of%20inflation%20picking%20up%20again%2C%20which%20would%20force%20the%20Fed%20to%20take%20more%20drastic%20measures%20to%20rein%20in%20prices.%20April's%20job%20report%20came%20in%20at%20175%2C000%20jobs%20created%2C%20weaker%20than%20the%20238%2C000%20expected%2C%20but%20employment%20stayed%20below%204%25%20and%20wage%20growth%20cooled.%20Wall%20Street%20loved%20that%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20growth%2C%20but%20not%20too%20much%20growth.%20Goldilocks%2C%20the%20weather%20on%20April%2025th%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bnot%20too%20cold%2C%20not%20too%20hot%2C%20all%20you%20need%20is%20a%20light%20jacket.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParadoxically%2C%20there%20are%20signs%20that%20things%20aren't%20as%20hunky-dory%20as%20they%20may%20appear.%20McDonald's%20missed%20quarterly%20earnings%20estimates%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20two%20years%20as%2C%20the%20company%20said%2C%20its%20customers%20were%20%26quot%3Bmore%20discriminating%20with%20every%20dollar%20they%20spend.%26quot%3B%20Starbucks%20saw%20sales%20decline%20for%20the%20first%20time%20since%202020%2C%20in%20what%20the%20company's%20CEO%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Bhighly%20challenging%20environment%26quot%3B%20surrounding%20%26quot%3Bpressures%20consumers%20face.%26quot%3B%20Over%20at%20Pepsi%2C%20organic%20sales%20fell%202%25.%20What%20all%20these%20companies%20have%20in%20common%20is%20that%20they%20had%20been%20able%20to%20extract%20more%20money%20from%20customers%20with%20significant%20price%20increases%20over%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20and%20now%20they%20can't.%20Money%20has%20tightened%2C%20and%20now%20they%20can't%20push%20price%20hikes%20over%20sales%20volume.%20Expect%20to%20see%20this%20theme%20repeat%20itself%20all%20over%20the%20market.%20The%20bad%20news%20is%20that%20this%20means%20the%20consumer%20%E2%80%94%20the%20engine%20of%20the%20US%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20is%20getting%20tired.%20The%20good%20news%20is%20that%20this%20means%20these%20companies%20won't%20be%20a%20source%20of%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20certainly%20hope%20that%20inflation%20has%20peaked%2C%26quot%3B%20Silas%20Myers%2C%20a%20cofounder%20and%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20investment%20firm%20Mar%20Vista%20Investments%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BBut%20we%20are%20seeing%20significant%20cracks%20in%20consumer%20spending%20at%20the%20lower%20end.%20People%20are%20trading%20down%20products.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20this%20contradictory%20information%20raises%20a%20lot%20of%20questions%20for%20Wall%20Street.%20Do%20we%20actually%20need%20more%20interest-rate%20hikes%2C%20or%20can%20the%20Fed%20just%20wait%20for%20things%20to%20settle%3F%20If%20we%20need%20to%20keep%20pushing%20to%20lower%20inflation%2C%20just%20how%20ugly%20will%20things%20get%3F%20What%20if%20the%20inflation%20pickup%20is%20a%20head%20fake%20and%2C%20actually%2C%20the%20economy%20is%20weakening%3F%20Is%20not%20cutting%20interest%20rates%20now%20a%20mistake%3F%20You%20can%20see%20why%20this%20tug-of-war%20will%20keep%20Wall%20Street%20on%20its%20toes%20and%20off%20Georgica%20Beach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20works%2C%20what%20doesn't%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20rate%20cuts%20seemed%20guaranteed%2C%20and%20Wall%20Street's%20betting%20class%20was%20lining%20up%20which%20oceanfront%20parties%20to%20hit%20this%20year%2C%20it%20seemed%20like%20the%20market%20would%20be%20easy%20picking%20this%20year.%20If%20rates%20fell%2C%20there%20would%20surely%20be%20more%20money%20sloshing%20around%20in%20the%20stock%20market%2C%20pushing%20up%20indexes%20and%20likely%20crowning%20the%20same%20winners%20as%20the%20year%20before.%20But%20as%20doubt%20about%20the%20economy%20crept%20into%20Wall%20Street's%20mind%2C%20so%2C%20too%2C%20did%20concern%20about%20these%20trades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHigher%20rates%20for%20longer%20means%20business%20models%20that%20used%20to%20work%20might%20not%20work%20anymore.%20Investors%20have%20to%20be%20a%20little%20more%20discerning.%20Bets%20that%20companies%20will%20develop%20tech%20and%20then%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20monetize%20it%20after%20the%20fact%20are%20already%20being%20punished%20compared%20with%20bets%20on%20disciplined%2C%20profit-focused%20operations.%20Take%20the%20%26quot%3BMagnificent%20Seven%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20group%20of%20tech%20stocks%20that%20dominated%20the%20market%20in%202023.%20The%20fortunes%20of%20these%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20Nvidia%2C%20Tesla%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20Meta%2C%20Apple%2C%20Amazon%2C%20and%20Alphabet%20%E2%80%94%20have%20diverged%20as%20the%20market%20got%20religion%20about%20the%20realities%20of%20the%20artificial-intelligence%20revolution.%20After%20Meta%20announced%20bumper%20earnings%20last%20month%2C%20investors%20sent%20its%20stock%20crashing%2010%25%20because%20the%20House%20of%20Zuck%20said%20it%20would%20spend%20%2435%20billion%20to%20%2440%20billion%20building%20an%20AI%20product%20this%20year.%20Exactly%20how%20that%20investment%20would%20be%20monetized%20it%20couldn't%20say.%20In%20a%20world%20where%20money%20is%20more%20expensive%2C%20those%20are%20the%20types%20of%20questions%20the%20market%20wants%20answered%20posthaste.%20Microsoft%20and%20Alphabet%2C%20which%20have%20already%20started%20monetizing%20their%20investments%2C%20fared%20much%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20really%20worried%20about%20a%20hawkish%20pivot%20because%20I%20think%20they%20own%20all%20the%20wrong%20stuff%2C%26quot%3B%20Simon%20said.%20When%20a%20trade%20is%20en%20vogue%20on%20Wall%20Street%2C%20you%20can%20expect%20everyone%20to%20crowd%20in%2C%20and%20if%20the%20trade%20reverses%2C%20you%20can%20expect%20a%20stampede%20to%20the%20exit.%20That%20ultimately%20creates%20market%20moves%20so%20dramatic%20they%20can%20push%20down%20indexes%20and%2C%20frankly%2C%20wreck%20a%20trader's%20day%20if%20they're%20not%20paying%20attention.%20So%20it's%20time%20to%20pay%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20new%20regime%20doesn't%20apply%20just%20to%20Wall%20Street's%20stock%20investors.%20The%20longer%20that%20higher%20rates%20in%20the%20US%20stick%20around%2C%20the%20more%20our%20monetary%20policy%20diverges%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world's.%20In%20the%20EU%20and%20the%20UK%2C%20inflation%20is%20receding%2C%20and%20rate%20policy%20looks%20like%20it's%20coming%20down.%20In%20Japan%2C%20interest%20rates%20are%20barely%20above%20zero.%20That%20divergence%20means%20major%20volatility%20as%20hot%20money%20sloshes%20around%20the%20world%20looking%20for%20the%20safest%20haven.%20As%20if%20to%20emphasize%20that%20fact%2C%20on%20the%20day%20of%20Powell's%20speech%2C%20the%20value%20of%20the%20Japanese%20yen%20blasted%20up%20against%20the%20dollar%20by%201%25%20in%20one%20second%20%E2%80%94%20a%20massive%20move%20by%20currency-trading%20standards%20and%20a%20vicious%20reversal%20given%20that%20over%20the%20past%20year%2C%20the%20yen%20has%20fallen%2011%25%20against%20the%20dollar.%20There%20is%20a%20certain%20set%20on%20Wall%20Street%20that%20does%20not%20get%20to%20%26quot%3Bros%C3%A9%20all%20day%26quot%3B%20on%20Hamptons%20summer%20water%20when%20currencies%20trade%20that%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20has%20always%20said%20there%20are%20%26quot%3Blong%20and%20variable%20lags%26quot%3B%20between%20when%20it%20moves%20interest%20rates%20and%20when%20the%20economy%20feels%20those%20moves.%20Now%20the%20Fed%20is%20starting%20to%20admit%20that%20those%20lags%20may%20be%20longer%20and%20more%20variable%20than%20it%20thought.%20The%20simplicity%20that%20Wall%20Street%20hoped%20for%20is%20one%20of%20the%20few%20options%20that's%20no%20longer%20on%20the%20table.%20Simple%20%E2%80%94%20like%20a%20cold%20glass%20of%20lemonade%20on%20the%20front%20porch%20or%20a%20%24210%20pitcher%20of%20Gimme%20Shelter%20at%20Sunset%20Beach%20%E2%80%94%20is%20what%20summer%20is%20made%20of.%20That's%20why%20this%20year%2C%20it's%20canceled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Flinette-lopez%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ELinette%20Lopez%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-summer-worry-stock-market-crash-inflation-hamtons-vacation-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714904822000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6633d4c00dfb1341e901f44b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-summer-worry-stock-market-crash-inflation-hamtons-vacation-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Forget%20the%20Hamptons%20and%20put%20down%20the%20ros%C3%A8%3A%20stubborn%20inflation%20and%20stock%20market%20volatility%20is%20making%20this%20Wall%20Street's%20summer%20of%20worry.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22llopez%40insider.com%20(Linette%20Lopez)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-summer-worry-stock-market-crash-inflation-hamtons-vacation-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BStop%20Doubting%26quot%3B%3A%20Google%20Engineer%20Who%20Failed%205%20Times%20Before%20Landing%20The%20Job%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20apply%20for%20jobs%20numerous%20times%20throughout%20their%20careers%20in%20the%20hopes%20of%20getting%20hired%20by%20their%20dream%20companies.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20story%20of%20a%20woman%20who%20never%20stopped%20trying%20and%20finally%20got%20a%20job%20at%20her%20dream%20organisation%20Google%20is%20inspiring%20people%20online.%20Qingyue%20Wang%2C%20who%20is%20now%20a%20software%20engineer%20at%20Google%2C%20shared%20experience%20and%20explained%20how%20she%20applied%20to%20the%20organisation%20in%202018%20and%20was%20hired%20in%202022%2C%20after%20not%20giving%20up.%20She%20asked%20people%20to%20%26quot%3Bstop%20blaming%20or%20doubting%26quot%3B%20themselves%20for%20not%20landing%20a%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20failed%20to%20get%20into%20Google%205%20times.%20The%201st%20time%20was%20in%202018.%20I%20received%20an%20online%20assessment%20from%20Google.%20I%20was%20excited%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20pass%20the%20OA.%20Afterwards%2C%20an%20interviewer%20reached%20out%20to%20me.%20They%20had%20reviewed%20my%20OA%20answers%20and%20wanted%20to%20give%20me%20a%20second%20chance.%20Unfortunately%2C%20I%20didn't%20pass%20on%20this%20attempt%20either%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20woman%20wrote%20on%20LinkedIn.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDescribing%20her%20other%20attempts%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BMy%203rd%20attempt%20was%20in%20early%202020.%20I%20had%20a%20phone%20screening%20interview%2C%20which%20I%20didn't%20pass.%20Persisting%2C%20I%20applied%20again%20in%202020%20for%20a%20Site%20Reliability%20Engineer%20role.%20After%20four%20rounds%20of%20interviews%20and%20receiving%20positive%20feedback%2C%20the%20role%20was%20unfortunately%20canceled%20due%20to%20the%20pandemic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fembed%2Ffeed%2Fupdate%2Furn%3Ali%3Ashare%3A7190731501188050944%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Embedded%20post%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22935%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Wang%20said%20that%20finally%2C%20on%20her%20fifth%20attempt%2C%20she%20passed%20the%20interview%20and%20received%20a%20gift%20from%20the%20tech%20giant.%20%26quot%3BIn%202022%2C%20on%20my%205th%20attempt%2C%20I%20finally%20secured%20a%20Software%20Engineer%20role.%20After%20passing%20the%20interview%2C%20I%20received%20a%20gift%20from%20Google%20along%20with%20a%20paper%20that%20said%2C%20'Congratulations%2C%20searching%20for%20a%20job%20is%20hard...'%20I've%20kept%20this%20paper%20for%202%20years%20now%20as%20it%20continually%20reminds%20me%20of%20the%20importance%20of%20persistence%20and%20not%20giving%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20engineer%20said%20that%20the%20job%20search%20process%20is%20not%20easy%20but%20one%20needs%20to%20work%20hard%20and%20look%20at%20the%20larger%20goal.%20She%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20stop%20blaming%20or%20doubting%20yourself%20if%20you%20once%20failed%20in%20your%20job%20search.%20The%20job%20search%20process%20can%20be%20complex%20and%20is%20often%20fraught%20with%20rejection%2C%20redirection%2C%20doubt%2C%20and%20frustration.%20However%2C%20persistence%20is%20typically%20a%20major%20factor%20and%20it's%20something%20within%20your%20control.%20Keep%20going%20-%20we're%20on%20this%20self-improvement%20journey%20together!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20being%20shared%2C%20her%20post%20has%20amassed%20over%20a%20lakh%20reactions%20on%20the%20networking%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20got%20rejected%207%20times%20..%20still%20trying%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20user.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20yeah.%20Google%20is%20tough%20to%20get%20into.%20I%20passed%20the%20Assessment%20and%20the%20interview%20but%20they%20still%20went%20with%20someone%20else%20recently.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20persevered%20through%20the%20jungle%20and%20emerged%20victorious!%20That%20Google%20rejection%20letter%20sounds%20like%20a%20hilarious%20(and%20well-deserved)%20trophy.%20Persistence%20is%20key%2C%20and%20your%20story%20is%20an%20inspiration%20to%20keep%20pushing%20forward.%20Onwards%20and%20upwards!%26quot%3B%20wrote%20a%20third%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20person%20commented%2C%20%26quot%3BHonestly%2C%20trying%20so%20hard%20to%20get%20a%20job%20at%20a%20company%20that%20clearly%20kept%20you%20on%20the%20hook%20without%20hiring%20you%20for%20so%20long%20isn't%20persistence%2C%20it's%20not%20seeing%20the%20red%20flags.%20While%20Google%20seems%20like%20the%20ultimate%20get%20for%20programmers%2C%20there%20are%20so%20many%20more%20companies%20out%20there%20that%20would%20recognize%20your%20talents%20way%20sooner.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714904820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2F7h4uagjo_qingyuewanglinkedin_625x300_05_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fstop-doubting-yourself-google-engineer-who-failed-5-times-before-landing-the-job-5593580%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20engineer%20said%20that%20the%20job%20search%20process%20is%20not%20easy%20but%20one%20needs%20to%20work%20hard%20and%20look%20at%20the%20larger%20goal.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fstop-doubting-yourself-google-engineer-who-failed-5-times-before-landing-the-job-5593580%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fstop-doubting-yourself-google-engineer-who-failed-5-times-before-landing-the-job-5593580%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fstop-doubting-yourself-google-engineer-who-failed-5-times-before-landing-the-job-5593580%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20drove%20Subaru's%20priciest%20SUV.%20It's%20perfect%20for%20families%20who%20outgrow%20the%20Outback%20or%20Forester%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20safety%20tech%20is%20vexing.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223533%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%202024%20Subaru%20Ascent%20Touring%20SUV%20in%20Dark%20M