d%20the%20top%20ride-hailing%20strategies%20he's%20tried%2C%20what%20worked%20and%20didn't%2C%20and%20another%20reason%20%E2%80%94%20in%20addition%20to%20a%20declining%20income%20%E2%80%94%20he's%20considering%20ditching%20ride-hailing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20strategies%20have%20been%20effective%2C%20but%20none%20have%20moved%20the%20needle%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGeorge%20said%20he's%20tried%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-lyft-florida-private-rides-miami-fort-lauderdale-spring-break-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echerry%20picking%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20only%20accepting%20trips%20that%20pay%20a%20minimum%20of%20%241%20a%20mile.%20But%20he%20said%20he%20often%20finds%20himself%20accepting%20rides%20below%20this%20threshold%20that%20take%20him%20to%20busier%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrivers%20have%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20it's%20easier%20to%20be%20picky%20with%20rides%20when%20one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-uber-drivers-make-fulltime-cancelling-rides-gig-economy-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edrives%20part-time%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20is%20less%20reliant%20on%20ride-hailing%20income.%20A%20low%20acceptance%20rate%20can%20also%20make%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uber.com%2Fhu%2Fen%2Fdrive%2Fuber-pro%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAcceptance%2520Rate%2C-If%2520you%2520are%26amp%3Btext%3Dearning%2520more%2520points.-%2CYou%2520will%2520maintain%2520your%2520current%2520status%2520and%2520have%2520access%2520to%2Cdid%2520I%2520get%2520my%2520status%253F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edifficult%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20drivers%20to%20retain%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-uber-drivers-make-fulltime-cancelling-rides-gig-economy-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edriver%20status%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20can%20provide%20perks%20like%20savings%20at%20select%20gas%2