%20daughter%20on%20my%20own.%20The%20experience%20of%20parenting%20my%20daughter%20was%20vastly%20different%20than%20parenting%20my%20two%20sons%2C%20who%20are%20now%2013%20and%2014.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20a%20partner%20now%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhaving-twins-created-more-equity-in-parenting-with-my-partner-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshares%20parenting%20responsibilities%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20decisions%20with%20me%2C%20but%20while%20raising%20my%20daughter%2C%20everything%20was%20on%20my%20shoulders.%20Having%20another%20invested%20person%20to%20look%20to%20and%20bounce%20things%20off%20of%20when%20I'm%20not%20sure%20about%20something%20is%20an%20entirely%20new%20experience.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20world%20is%20also%20different.%20Technology%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffounders-disrupting-social-media-networking-landscape-new-apps-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esocial%20media%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20evolved%2C%20presenting%20new%20conveniences%20and%20timesavers%2C%20and%20also%20new%20things%20to%20worry%20about%2C%20like%20comparing%20our%20parenting%20to%20everyone%20else's.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESocial%20media%20makes%20us%20compare%20each%20other's%20parenting%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20people%20found%20out%20I%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-single-mom-did-her-best-raising-me-im-grateful-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20single%20parent%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20typical%20response%20was%2C%20%26quot%3BWow%2C%20that%20must%20be%20so%20tough.%26quot%3B%20I%20rarely%20thought%20of%20it%20that%20way%2C%20although%20I%20remember%20being%20lonely%20and%20broke.%20Looking%20back%2C%20I%20think%20being%20a%20single%20mom%20was%20hard.%20However%2C%20I%20think%20today's%20solo%20parents%20have%20a%20more%20difficult%20time%20due%20to%20the%20pressures%20of%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20discovered%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fa-mom-shares-how-facebook-parenting-groups-can-be-lifesaving-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFacebook%20mom%20groups%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20my%20two%20youngest%20children%20were%20small.%20We%20adopted%20our%20boys%20in%202012%20and%202013%2C%20and%20there%20was%20a%20Facebook%20mom%20group%20for%20everything.%20Adoptive%20moms%2C%20boy%20moms%2C%20toddler%20moms%2C%20all%20types%20of%20parenting%20styles%20%E2%80%94%20you%20name%20it%2C%20there%20was%20a%20ready-made%20Facebook%20community%20for%20it.%20At%20first%2C%20I%20was%20thrilled%20to%20have%20found%20a%20network%20that%20would%20make%20me%20feel%20less%20isolated.%20Then%20I%20started%20noticing%20the%20snarky%2C%20thinly%20veiled%20criticisms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparenting-styles-from-around-the-world-2018-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompared%20my%20performance%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20mom%20to%20complete%20strangers%20on%20Instagram%2C%20wondering%20why%20no%20one%20else%20had%20a%20train%20wreck%20of%20a%20dirty%20kitchen%20and%20whether%20I%20was%20failing%20because%20I%20wasn't%20color-coordinating%20our%20outfits%20to%20go%20to%20the%20grocery%20store.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20sure%20if%20I%20would%20have%20been%20able%20to%20take%20so%20many%20things%20with%20so%20many%20grains%20of%20salt%20back%20when%20I%20was%20in%20my%2020s%20and%20a%20single%20mom.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20see%20a%20picture-perfect%20family%20on%20social%20media%2C%20it's%20easy%20to%20let%20myself%20feel%20inferior%20and%20mentally%20list%20the%20things%20they're%20doing%20right%20that%20I'm%20doing%20wrong%2C%20but%20I'm%20usually%20able%20to%20curb%20that%20urge%20to%20compare%20too%20strongly.%20I%20remind%20myself%20that%20I've%20posted%20some%20things%20on%20social%20media%20that%20aren't%20representative%20of%20what's%20really%20happening%20in%20my%20life%20and%20that%20other%20people%20are%20probably%20doing%20the%20same.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFor%20me%2C%20loneliness%20was%20the%20hardest%20thing%20about%20being%20a%20single%20mom%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hardest%20thing%20about%20solo%20parenting%20my%20daughter%20was%20limited%20adult%20interaction.%20I%20got%20my%20social%20fix%20at%20work%20during%20the%20day%2C%20but%20I%20would%20have%20liked%20someone%20to%20talk%20to%20after%20she%20went%20to%20bed%20at%20night.%20Being%20lonely%2C%20while%20never%20being%20alone%2C%20is%20something%20that%20surprised%20me%20about%20being%20a%20single%20parent%20and%20something%20definitely%20not%20in%20the%20manual.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20often%20felt%20like%20my%20personal%20identity%20was%20limited%20to%20being%20a%20mom%20and%20that%20outside%20cutting%20the%20crusts%20off%20of%20sandwiches%20and%20reading%20%26quot%3BAmelia%20Bedelia%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20didn't%20really%20know%20who%20I%20was.%20%26quot%3BWork%20me%26quot%3B%20was%20serious%20and%20hardworking%2C%20trying%20to%20erase%20my%20mom%20persona%20while%20on%20the%20job.%20I%20knew%20a%20few%20other%20moms%2C%20but%20we%20were%20mostly%20too%20busy%20and%20exhausted%20to%20make%20time%20for%20friendships.%20The%20concept%20of%20self-care%20wasn't%20as%20widespread%20as%20it%20is%20today%2C%20and%20nobody%20really%20talked%20about%20what%20moms%20needed.%20I%20got%20it%20all%20done.%20My%20daughter%20was%20thriving%2C%20and%20I%20advanced%20at%20work%2C%20but%20there%20was%20always%20that%20pervasive%20sense%20of%20aloneness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20sometimes%20wonder%20how%20my%20experience%20parenting%20my%20daughter%20in%20the%2090s%20would%20have%20been%20made%20better%20or%20worse%20by%20the%20presence%20of%20social%20media.%20My%20experience%20with%20Facebook%20mom%20groups%20has%20taught%20me%20that%20they're%20mostly%20a%20place%20of%20judgment%20and%20one-upmanship.%20Still%2C%20there%20are%20nuggets%20of%20connection%20in%20there%20if%20you%20can%20handle%20weeding%20through%20the%20noise%20and%20occasional%20snark.%20I%20wonder%20if%20I%20was%20better%20off%20being%20isolated%20on%20my%20own%20island%20than%20I%20would%20have%20been%20connected%20to%20a%20digital%20environment%20that%20had%20the%20potential%20to%20be%20toxic.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20I%20envy%20today's%20single%20moms%20a%20little%20bit.%20People%20are%20more%20used%20to%20solo%20parents%2C%20and%20it%20seems%20more%20%26quot%3Bnormal.%26quot%3B%20And%2C%20whether%20we%20call%20having%20access%20to%20an%20online%20community%20of%20moms%20that%20might%20be%20unhealthy%2C%20I%20like%20the%20fact%20that%20there's%20a%20choice%20now.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%2C%20in%20that%20sea%20of%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20believe%20you're%20giving%20your%20kid%20that%20much%20sugar%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BDoes%20anyone%20know%20what%20this%20rash%20is%3F%26quot%3B%20I%20would%20have%20been%20able%20to%20find%20my%20people.%20I'll%20never%20know%20for%20sure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-parenting-lonely-no-social-media-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714903382000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6626978a83c8ec6e1530a674%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-parenting-lonely-no-social-media-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I%20was%20a%20single%20mom%20in%20the%2090s%20before%20there%20was%20social%20media.%20I%20missed%20out%20on%20virtual%20communities%20but%20also%20didn't%20compare%20myself%20to%20others.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Jill%20Robbins)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-parenting-lonely-no-social-media-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mortgage%20Interest%20Rates%20Today%2C%20May%205%2C%202024%2