nd-Aid%20method%2C%20Rich%20simply%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BBoys%2C%20I've%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoffs-firings-tech-hr-tiktok-cloudflare-employee-morale-bad-business-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeen%20laid%20off%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOur%20kids%20had%20a%20hard%20time%20understanding%20what%20had%20happened%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%2C%20wait%2C%20wait%2C%20Dad%20was%20fired%3F%26quot%3B%20Ben%20jumped%20off%20the%20couch.%20There%20it%20was.%20A%20one-kid%20game%20of%20telephone.%20A%20single%20sentence%20and%20a%20message%20badly%20boggled.%20Charlie%20giggled%20at%20his%20brother's%20dramatic%20outburst.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%2C%20my%20department%20is%20restructuring%2C%26quot%3B%20Rich%20said%20calmly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWell%2C%20if%20it's%20your%20department%2C%20why%20aren't%20you%20still%20there%3F%20How%20can%20it%20be%20yours%20and%20then%20they%20kick%20you%20out%3F%20That's%20totally%20not%20fair%2C%26quot%3B%20Ben%20shouted%20as%20he%20struggled%20to%20understand%2C%20his%20tiny%20body%20rigid%20with%20indignation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20just%20mean%20the%20group%20I%20was%20part%20of%20decided%20that%20they%20don't%20need%20as%20many%20people%20anymore%2C%26quot%3B%20Rich%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWait%2C%20Mom%20still%20has%20her%20job%2C%20right%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20asked.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20good.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBen%2C%20are%20you%20crazy%3F%20Mom's%20job%20pays%20like%20no%20money.%20And%20it's%20part-time!%26quot%3B%20Sam%20rolled%20his%20eyes%20toward%20the%20ceiling%20in%20disgust.%20At%2011%2C%20he'd%20already%20mastered%20the%20sarcastic%20tone%20of%20a%20grown%20man.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20that%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcorporate-america-companies-part-time-jobs-work-layoffs-great-resignation-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworked%20part-time%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20a%20common%20misconception%20in%20our%20home.%20I%20worked%20at%20a%20startup%20company%20as%20a%20reporter%20and%20editor%20for%20several%20local%20news%20websites%2C%20and%20the%20job%20often%20demanded%20over%2060%20hours%20a%20week.%20But%20because%20I%20tried%20to%20do%20the%20bulk%20of%20my%20work%20while%20the%20boys%20were%20at%20school%20or%20in%20bed%2C%20they%20assumed%20it%20was%20a%20little%20hobby%20for%20me%20%E2%80%94%20as%20if%20anyone%20would%20voluntarily%20cover%20four-hour%20school%20board%20meetings%20or%20report%20on%20grisly%20drunk-driving%20accidents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fside-hustle-cured-my-burnout-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estarted%20out%20freelancing%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20an%20editor%20at%20the%20company%20recommended%20me%20for%20a%20permanent%20role.%20After%20a%20grueling%20four-hour%20writing%20test%20and%20multiple%20phone%20and%20in-person%20interviews%2C%20I%20was%20offered%20a%20full-time%20position%20with%20benefits%20and%20a%20401(k).%20I'd%20been%20in%20this%20job%20for%20more%20than%20two%20years.%20It%20was%20intense%2C%20but%20I%20was%20constantly%20learning%20and%20meeting%20interesting%20people.%20Yet%20the%20company%20had%20grown%20too%20big%20too%20fast%20and%20was%20struggling%20to%20turn%20profitable%20as%20quickly%20as%20it%20hoped.%20There%20seemed%20to%20be%20a%20new%20round%20of%20layoffs%20every%20few%20months.%20It%20caught%20those%20of%20us%20who%20remained%20off%20guard%20and%20weakened%20our%20morale.%20I'd%20somehow%20escaped%20a%20pink%20slip%2C%20but%20I%20feared%20my%20luck%20would%20eventually%20run%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYes%2C%20I%20still%20have%20my%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20told%20the%20boys%20as%20I%20added%20a%20wistful%20%26quot%3Bfor%20now%26quot%3B%20under%20my%20breath.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20all%20going%20to%20be%20fine.%26quot%3B%20Rich%20recited%20his%20new%20incantation%20once%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESam%20looked%20at%20me%2C%20doubt%20darkening%20his%20eyes.%20He%20wanted%20me%20to%20validate%20his%20father's%20%26quot%3BNothing-to-see-here!%26quot%3B%20attitude.%20Even%20as%20a%20preteen%2C%20he%20seemed%20to%20possess%20enough%20sense%20to%20wonder%2C%20%26quot%3BCan%20a%20middle-aged%20man%20get%20another%20job%20that%20easily%3F%26quot%3B%20I%20wanted%20to%20reassure%20him%20but%20not%20misrepresent%20the%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20knew%20what%20it%20was%20like%20%E2%80%94%20my%20dad%20had%20been%20laid%20off%2C%20too%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20own%20dad%20had%20been%20let%20go%20from%20his%20career%20in%20his%20mid-50s.%20It%20hadn't%20seemed%20scary%20to%20me%20at%20the%20time%2C%20maybe%20because%20I%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdaughter-heading-college-considered-moving-close-campus-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaway%20at%20college%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20didn't%20have%20to%20see%20him%20looking%20defeated%20when%20he'd%20been%20replaced%20by%20someone%20half%20his%20age%20who'd%20happily%20accepted%20a%20quarter%20of%20his%20salary.%20But%20I%20think%20my%20lack%20of%20alarm%20was%20mainly%20because%20I%20knew%20my%20dad%20had%20been%20investing%20since%20the%20moment%20he'd%20received%20his%20First%20Holy%20Communion%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20own%20father%20had%20died%20from%20a%20heart%20condition%20when%20my%20dad%20was%20just%202%20years%20old.%20He%20spent%20his%20early%20years%20riding%20shotgun%20in%20his%20grandfather's%20taxi%20so%20his%20mom%20could%20go%20to%20work%20as%20a%20beautician.%20They'd%20barely%20scraped%20by.%20Sometimes%2C%20they'd%20return%20home%20after%20a%20long%20day%20to%20find%20their%20electricity%20had%20been%20turned%20off%20because%20his%20mom%20had%20been%20forced%20to%20choose%20between%20rent%20or%20utilities.%20This%20constant%20financial%20stress%20made%20my%20dad%20hungry%20and%20ambitious.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe'd%20worked%20two%20jobs%20to%20put%20himself%20through%20college%20because%20he%20was%20determined%20to%20create%20a%20better%20life%20for%20his%20family.%20And%20while%20it%20had%20paid%20off%2C%20we%20lived%20modestly.%20My%20father%20had%20built%20a%20successful%20career%20heading%20up%20IT%20departments%20for%20various%20large%20insurance%20companies%20and%20saved%20every%20penny%20because%20he%20valued%20security%20more%20than%20a%20fancy%20house%20or%20luxury%20car.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mother%20had%20a%20similar%20mentality.%20In%20her%20mind%2C%20couponing%20and%20hoarding%20sale%20items%20were%20elevated%20to%20extreme%20sports.%20So%20when%20my%20dad%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-employee-laid-off-twice-tough-industry-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewas%20laid%20off%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20was%20certain%20they'd%20be%20fine.%20Here%20was%20the%20rainy%20day%20they'd%20been%20saving%20for.%20It%20had%20felt%20more%20like%20a%20self-fulfilling%20prophecy%20than%20a%20cause%20for%20panic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20I%20looked%20back%2C%20it%20occurred%20to%20me%20that%20even%20with%20his%20vast%20experienc%2C%20my%20dad%20had%20never%20worked%20full-time%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20tried%20to%20reassure%20them%20that%20everything%20would%20be%20fine%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20all%20going%20to%20be%20fine!%26quot%3B%20Rich%20said%20again%2C%20reminding%20me%20of%20how%20he'd%20earned%20the%20nickname%20Deuces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20he'd%20been%20in%20the%20financial%20news%20business%20for%20two%20decades%2C%20I%20suddenly%20wondered%20if%20we%20were%20privy%20to%20the%20same%20economic%20information.%20I%20knew%20a%20%3Cem%3Elot%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20people%20who%20had%20been%20out%20of%20work%20and%20struggled%20to%20find%20new%20positions.%20Why%20wasn't%20he%20more%20concerned%3F%20Once%20the%20safety%20net%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-layoffs-severance-agreement-pay-benefits-details-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseverance%20package%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20gone%2C%20we'd%20face%20a%20shortfall%20of%20almost%20%248%2C000%20a%20month.%20Yes%2C%20that%20was%2013%20months%20from%20now%2C%20but%20time%20seemed%20to%20speed%20up%20with%20each%20passing%20year.%20It%20felt%20like%20only%20yesterday%20that%20Sam%20was%20born.%20Now%2C%20at%20five%20feet%2C%20five%20inches%2C%20he%20and%20I%20were%20nearly%20the%20same%20height.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWho%20wants%20ice%20cream%3F%26quot%3B%20asked%20Rich%2C%20knowing%20that%20would%20bring%20all%20questions%20to%20an%20abrupt%20halt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESam%20and%20Ben%20dashed%20to%20the%20kitchen%20with%20Charlie%20on%20their%20heels%2C%20ever%20the%20little%20brother.%20They%20elbowed%20one%20another%20to%20get%20through%20the%20narrow%20kitchen%20doorway%20first%2C%20each%20determined%20to%20out-scoop%20his%20brothers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSee%3F%26quot%3B%20Rich%20said%20to%20me%20over%20the%20clatter%20of%20bowls%20and%20spoons%2C%20the%20slam%20of%20the%20freezer%20door%2C%20and%20Ben%20calling%20dibs%20on%20the%20Cool%20Whip.%20%26quot%3BEverything%20is%20going%20to%20be%20just%20fine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20the%20children%20wanted%20hot-fudge%20sundaes%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20believe%20him.%20But%20I%20didn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EExcerpted%20from%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D903c6392ed2420b9fd3f80626b79d9725c270162f76fed047d99056f86261fbd%26postID%3D66329ca9a7714381cef173f7%26postSlug%3Dhusband-laid-off-how-to-tell-kids-2024-5%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FSad-Sacked-Liz-Alterman%252Fdp%252F398832065X%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3ESad%20Sacked%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3B%20by%20Liz