%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-social-security-gen-z-millennials-uncertainty-fears-pensions-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmericans%20gravitated%20toward%20defined-contribution%3C%2Fa%3E%20plans%20%E2%80%94%20like%20401(k)s%20%E2%80%94%20instead%20of%20defined-benefit%20plans%20like%20pensions.%20This%20has%20shifted%20more%20responsibility%20onto%20employees%20to%20determine%20how%20much%20to%20invest%20and%20save.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPut%20simply%2C%20the%20shift%20from%20defined%20benefit%20to%20defined%20contribution%20has%20been%2C%20for%20most%20people%2C%20a%20shift%20from%20financial%20certainty%20to%20financial%20uncertainty%2C%26quot%3B%20BlackRock%20CEO%20Larry%20Fink%20wrote%20in%20a%202024%20letter%20to%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMillions%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-x-baby-boomers-savings-cant-afford-retirement-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebaby%20boomers%20now%20struggle%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20cover%20their%20cost%20of%20living.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpress.aarp.org%2F2024-4-24-New-AARP-Survey-1-in-5-Americans-Ages-50-Have-No-Retirement-Savings%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAARP%20survey%20in%20April%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20one%20in%20five%20Americans%20who%20are%2050%20or%20older%20have%20no%20retirement%20savings%2C%20and%20more%20than%20half%20of%20respondents%20were%20concerned%20they%20wouldn't%20have%20enough%20to%20support%20themselves%20if%20they%20retired.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20as%20retirement%20in%20the%20United%20States%20gets%20bleak%2C%20some%20Americans%20are%20looking%20elsewhere.%20Specifically%2C%20they%20are%20looking%20to%20Italy%2C%20which%20ranks%20among%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.in%2Fpolicy%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fthese-countries-have-the-most-generous-retirement-plans-in-the-world%2Farticleshow%2F104527568.cms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etop%2020%20countrie