strong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPatrizia%20Di%20Gregorio%20has%20witnessed%20the%20uptick%20in%20people%2C%20including%20Americans%2C%20looking%20to%20retire%20in%20Italy%20firsthand.%20Gregorio%2C%2052%2C%20is%20an%20Italian-American%20who%20founded%20the%20international%20social%20network%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.expatslivinginrome.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EExpats%20Living%20in%20Rome%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202001.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20network%20has%20become%20an%20essential%20tool%20for%20people%20across%20the%20globe%20eyeing%20a%20move%20to%20Italy.%20The%20organization%20offers%20resources%20for%20those%20looking%20to%20move%2C%20including%20financial%20guidance%20and%20immigration%20advice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222260%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Expats%20Living%20in%20Room%20website.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66355039ec0c696569010d78%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221462%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EScreenshot%20of%20the%20Expats%20Living%20in%20Room%20website.%3Cp%3EExpats%20Living%20in%20Room%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20offers%20a%20community%20through%20Facebook%20groups%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fexpatsinrome%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EExpats%20Living%20in%20Rome%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fgroups%2Fexpatslivinginitaly%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EExpats%20Living%20in%20Italy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20people%20can%20ask%20questions%20and%20share%20updates%20on%20their%20journeys.%20The%20Expats%20Living%20in%20Italy%20group%20now%20has%20more%20than%20107%2C000%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGregorio%20told%20BI%20she%20first%20noticed%20increased%20interest%20from%20Americans%20around%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Patrizia%20Di%20Gregorio%20(Expats%20Living%20in%20Rome)%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b976957a3d271488760434%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPatrizia%20Di%20Gregorio.%20%3Cp%3EPatrizia%20Di%20Gregorio%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBefore%20COVID%2C%20we%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20immigration%2C%20but%20after%20COVID%2C%20we%20can't%20even%20keep%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20She%20said%20that%20one%20Facebook%20group%20she%20created%20had%20more%20than%20800%20requests%20to%20join%20at%20one%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EExpats%20said%20Americans%20live%20to%20work%20but%20that%20in%20Italy%2C%20they%20work%20to%20live%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmistakes-americans-make-when-moving-to-italy-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMoving%20to%20Italy%20as%20an%20American%20isn't%20without%20challenges%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20series%20of%20hurdles%20must%20be%20cleared%3A%20securing%20a%20visa%2C%20finding%20a%20property%2C%20transporting%20goods%20across%20the%20Atlantic%20Ocean%2C%20applying%20for%20necessities%20like%20healthcare%2C%20and%20%E2%80%94%20of%20course%20%E2%80%94%20navigating%20a%20language%20barrier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20Schwendemans%20and%20Dukinfield%20are%20working%20to%20become%20fluent%20in%20Italian%20%E2%80%94%20which%20can%20sometimes%20make%20everyday%20tasks%20more%20arduous%20%E2%80%94%20but%20said%20leaving%20the%20United%20States%20was%20the%20right%20choice.%20They%20cited%20a%20better%20quality%20of%20life%2C%20which%20is%20no%20longer%20bogged%20down%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhustle-culture-got-america-addicted-to-work%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerica's%20unforgiving%20and%20overarching%20hustle%20culture.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Eric%20and%20Christina%20Schwendeman%20in%20Clavesana.%20%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66354dadec0c696569010c1b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEric%20and%20Christina%20Schwendeman.%3Cp%3EEric%20and%20Christina%20Schwendeman%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20way%20they%20approach%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Eric%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20Italian%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Clavesana%2C%20locals%20take%20%26quot%3Bpausa%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20two-hour%20break%20each%20afternoon%2C%20which%20contrasts%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fquickbooks.intuit.com%2Ftime-tracking%2Fresources%2Flunch-break-survey%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaverage%20lunch%20break%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20which%20is%2036%20minutes.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20stop%20working%2C%26quot%3B%20Eric%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20go%20have%20lunch%20with%20your%20family%20and%20your%20friends.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDukinfield%20agreed%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20slower%20pace%20of%20life%20and%20living%20in%20a%20walkable%20city%20have%20been%20positive%20changes.%20Moving%20to%20Vicenza%20has%20also%20allowed%20her%20to%20live%20near%20her%20daughter%2C%20son-in-law%2C%20and%20grandchild.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20walk%20to%20the%20downtown%20area%2C%26quot%3B%20Dukinfield%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20lived%20in%20a%20very%20nice%20house%20on%20a%20nice%20lot%20in%20suburbia%20%5Bin%20the%20US%5D%2C%20but%20the%20only%20place%20we%20could%20walk%20to%20was%20the%20Super%20America%20or%20the%20Speedway%2C%20which%20was%20three-quarters%20of%20a%20mile%20away.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20phenomenon%20Eric%20described%20is%20a%20popular%20phrase%20among%20US%20expats%3A%20In%20America%2C%20you%20live%20to%20work.%20In%20Italy%2C%20you%20work%20to%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20to%20say%20it's%20pretty%20much%20a%20total%20dream%2C%26quot%3B%20Christina%20said.%20%